[The letters 451-3 and 455 hang closely together and may be dated 1516. because of the New Testament (Ep. 384Â³, and because in no other year did Erasmus leave England in August. This letter, which was left behind with More in London (Ep. 452. 10), is probably not long prior to Ep. 452, since both are answered by Ep. 453. The Monday mentioned in l. 5 may therefore be taken as 11 August.]
